,\n46\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_put_requires_auth\",\n47\t        \"reason\": \"Both missing and malformed Bearer tokens get 401.\"\n48\t      },\n49\t      {\n50\t        \"id\": \"AC5\",\n51\t        \"covered\": true,\n52\t        \"test\": \"tests/test_schemas_quotas.py (parametrized) + tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_validation_rejections\",\n53\t        \"reason\": \"0/-1/-1000/non-integer limit, unknown field, and bad customer_id all assert 422 validation_failed at both the unit-schema and endpoint layers.\"\n54\t      },\n55\t      {\n56\t        \"id\": \"AC6\",\n57\t        \"covered\": true,\n58\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_quota_is_tenant_isolated + tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py (both tests)\",\n59\t        \"reason\": \"The endpoint test proves the app-level api_key_id scoping keeps two tenants' rows independent. Independently added this session: test_quotas_rls_backstop.py proves the DB-level RLS BACKSTOP itself (not just the app filter) -- it connects as a provisioned NOBYPASSRLS role (mirroring the production meterly_app role, not the testcontainers superuser, which always bypasses RLS) and issues queries with the api_key_id predicate REMOVED ENTIRELY (the primary control disabled), asserting the RLS policy alone still confines reads/updates to the caller's own tenant, and that an unset tenant setting fails closed (zero rows) rather than defaulting open. This satisfies the adversarial-test-shapes requirement that a backstop control must be proven with the primary control off, not merely declared.\"\n60\t      },\n61\t      {\n62\t        \"id\": \"AC7\",\n63\t        \"covered\": true,\n64\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_no_quota_is_unlimited\",\n65\t        \"reason\": \"No quota row -> 201 for a very large quantity, no regression.\"\n66\t      },\n67\t      {\n68\t        \"id\": \"AC8\",\n69\t        \"covered\": true,\n70\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_under_limit_accepted\",\n71\t        \"reason\": \"R+Q<=L -> 201, rollup total verified via direct SQL read.\"\n72\t      },\n73\t      {\n74\t        \"id\": \"AC9\",\n75\t        \"covered\": true,\n76\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_over_limit_429_and_no_partial_write\",\n77\t        \"reason\": \"429 quota_exceeded + Retry-After >= 1s; direct SQL proves the rejected event left no row and the rollup only reflects the accepted event (transaction rolled back).\"\n78\t      },\n79\t      {\n80\t        \"id\": \"AC10\",\n81\t        \"covered\": true,\n82\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_empty_window_q_gt_l_rejected\",\n83\t        \"reason\": \"First event in an empty window with Q>L -> 429; direct SQL proves zero rollup rows created.\"\n84\t      },\n85\t      {\n86\t        \"id\": \"AC11\",\n87\t        \"covered\": true,\n88\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_replay_over_quota_returns_200_no_usage\",\n89\t        \"reason\": \"A replay after the quota is lowered below the accumulated total still returns 200 with idempotent_replay=true and event_count stays 1 (quota never consulted on replay).\"\n90\t      },\n91\t      {\n92\t        \"id\": \"AC12\",\n93\t        \"covered\": true,\n94\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_midwindow_change_takes_effect\",\n95\t        \"reason\": \"Lowering L below the already-accumulated R blocks the very next POST (429) -- fresh-read-per-request proven.\"\n96\t      },\n97\t      {\n98\t        \"id\": \"AC13\",\n99\t        \"covered\": true,\n100\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quota_concurrency.py::test_concurrent_posts_never_exceed_limit\",\n101\t        \"reason\": \"20 concurrent distinct-idempotency-key posts against L=10 land exactly 10 winners/10 rejections (429 quota_exceeded), and the final rollup total via direct SQL never exceeds L -- asserts the loser's outcome, not merely a single-winner count.\"\n102\t      },\n103\t      {\n104\t        \"id\": \"AC14\",\n105\t        \"covered\": true,\n106\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_throttle_precedes_quota_distinct_codes\",\n107\t        \"reason\": \"Tier-2 throttle fires first (code=rate_limited) via the full request lifecycle (not a unit test of the key generator); a genuinely quota-exceeded call on a separate untouched-throttle key returns the distinct quota_exceeded code.\"\n108\t      },\n109\t      {\n110\t        \"id\": \"AC15\",\n111\t        \"covered\": true,\n112\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_put_rate_limited_per_principal\",\n113\t        \"reason\": \"Two admin principals sharing one client IP (10.0.0.9) get independent Tier-2 buckets -- the discriminating two-principals-one-IP shape, not a same-owner-different-IP weak form.\"\n114\t      },\n115\t      {\n116\t        \"id\": \"AC16\",\n117\t        \"covered\": true,\n118\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quota_migration.py::test_0003_roundtrip_schema_and_constraints\",\n119\t        \"reason\": \"Seeds 2 api_keys rows + a quotas row, runs up->down(0002)->up, asserts: quotas table (create-migration) is fully absent after down (schema-only reversibility, no row-survival claim); the 2 pre-existing api_keys rows survive with scope resetting to the 'ingest' default (expand/contract add-column contract); and after re-up, every constraint (PK duplicate, FK to nonexistent api_key, CHECK limit>=1 for 0 and -5, and api_keys.scope CHECK) is independently re-driven and rejected -- not merely asserted present in a schema dump.\"\n120\t      },\n121\t      {\n122\t        \"id\": \"AC17\",\n123\t        \"covered\": true,\n124\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_seed_api_key_script.py::test_admin_flag_sets_scope\",\n125\t        \"reason\": \"--admin sets scope='admin'; omitting it defaults to 'ingest'.\"\n126\t      },\n127\t      {\n128\t        \"id\": \"AC18\",\n129\t        \"covered\": true,\n130\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_injection_rejected_at_boundary + tests/test_schemas_quotas.py::test_rejects_injection_and_oversized_customer_id/test_rejects_invalid_metric (+ Hypothesis property test)\",\n131\t        \"reason\": \"SQLi/path-traversal/CRLF/oversized payloads in customer_id and metric are rejected at the Pydantic boundary (422) before reaching quotas_repo's parameterized text() sinks; the Hypothesis property test additionally proves any customer_id that DOES parse matches the anchored allowlist over generated inputs, not fixed examples.\"\n132\t      },\n133\t      {\n134\t        \"id\": \"AC19\",\n135\t        \"covered\": true,\n136\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_rejection_is_logged_without_totals + tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_upsert_and_forbidden_logged\",\n137\t        \"reason\": \"quota.rejected (WARNING, no current_total/limit fields), quota.upsert, and quota.forbidden are each asserted present in structlog JSON stdout.\"\n138\t      },\n139\t      {\n140\t        \"id\": \"AC20\",\n141\t        \"covered\": false,\n142\t        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_perf_k6_load.py::test_events_ingest_with_quotas_p95_under_50ms\",\n143\t        \"reason\": \"The test runs a real grafana/k6 Docker load (500 target rps, 15s measurement) against the quota-active POST /v1/events path and computes a true nearest-rank p95 over raw per-request samples (5493 samples, all 201s) -- but the test itself only asserts sample_count>0 (weak form), not the 50ms budget. Measured p95 this run was 3362.32ms, far exceeding the 50ms budget -- and substantially worse than this same host's baseline (no-quota) p95 of 83.55ms on the pre-existing AC6 ingest test, so this is not attributable solely to the known Docker-Desktop/Windows host.docker.internal overhead already flagged as a deferred finding on feature 1 (see MEMORY feature1_shipped_findings) -- the quota FOR UPDATE read-and-decide path appears to add substantial latency under sustained concurrent load across 50 customer buckets. Left uncovered rather than fabricating a pass; routes to debugging/human review.\"\n144\t      },\n145\t      {\n146\t        \"id\": \"AC21\",\n147\t        \"covered\": true,\n148\t        \"test\": \"tests/test_dast_context_documented.py::test_bearer_split_token_auth_context_is_documented + tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_openapi_exposes_put_quotas\",\n149\t        \"reason\": \"The served /openapi.json includes PUT /v1/quotas, and the DAST auth-context doc test confirms the Bearer mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret> scheme is documented; docs/system_architecture.md documents the admin test-key requirement (seed_api_key.py --admin).\"\n150\t      },\n151\t      {\n152\t        \"id\": \"AC22\",\n153\t        \"covered\": false,\n154\t        \"test\": null,\n155\t        \"reason\": \"ASVS reconciliation is the security stage's deliverable, not a test-suite assertion.\",\n156\t        \"delegated\": \"security\"\n157\t      }\n158\t    ]\n159\t  },\n160\t  \"resilience\": {\n161\t    \"migration_roundtrip\": \"pass\",\n162\t    \"property_tests\": 1,\n163\t    \"concurrency\": \"pass\"\n164\t  },\n165\t  \"perf\": {\n166\t    \"budget\": {\n167\t      \"p95_ms\": 50,\n168\t      \"throughput_rps\": null\n169\t    },\n170\t    \"measured\": {\n171\t      \"p95_ms\": 3362.32,\n172\t      \"throughput_rps\": 347.27\n173\t    },\n174\t    \"scenario\": {\n175\t      \"harness\": \"grafana/k6 via Docker, out-of-process uvicorn reached via host.docker.internal, constant-arrival-rate scenario\",\n176\t      \"target_rps\": 500,\n177\t      \"achieved_rps\": 347.27,\n178\t      \"duration\": \"5s warmup + 15s measurement\",\n179\t      \"workload\": \"POST /v1/events against 50 pre-seeded customer_id buckets, each with a high-but-finite quota (limit never exceeded) so the FOR UPDATE quota read-and-decide runs on every request without ever rejecting\",\n180\t      \"contention\": \"quota row lock (FOR UPDATE) taken per request across 50 distinct (api_key_id, customer_id, metric) rows, not a single hot lock\",\n181\t      \"sample_count\": 5493,\n182\t      \"status_counts\": {\n183\t        \"201\": 5493\n184\t      },\n185\t      \"optional_egress\": \"none\",\n186\t      \"note\": \"achieved throughput (347 rps) fell short of the 500 rps target and p95 (3362ms) is ~40x the pre-existing no-quota baseline p95 (83.55ms) measured on this same host in the same session -- see AC20 reason for the full comparison.\"\n187\t    },\n188\t    \"status\": \"fail\"\n189\t  },\n190\t  \"coverage\": {\n191\t    \"combined\": {\n192\t      \"lines\": 90.3,\n193\t      \"branches\": 58.3,\n194\t      \"functions\": null\n195\t    },\n196\t    \"unit\": {\n197\t      \"lines\": null,\n198\t      \"branches\": null\n199\t    },\n200\t    \"integration\": {\n201\t      \"lines\": null,\n202\t      \"branches\": null\n203\t    }\n204\t  }\n205\t}\n206\t"}]},"uuid":"6527b844-2025-42c6-87b9-35dcb4dc8462","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:28:25.430Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"cd1aeca3-4bd6-48e6-95e4-11d1e6609c36","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
