{"parentUuid":"f9ec3ef5-3a8c-43f1-b2a8-45eb64b6dee9","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a2d9a0c1af7d25884","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqmsmYon5QAfJJLLjzK1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01PLt4DsVumPWbmLHUZw39ek","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\test-results.json","old_string":"      {\n        \"id\": \"AC20\",\n        \"covered\": false,\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_perf_k6_load.py::test_events_ingest_with_quotas_p95_under_50ms\",\n        \"reason\": \"The test runs a real grafana/k6 Docker load (500 target rps, 15s measurement) against the quota-active POST /v1/events path and computes a true nearest-rank p95 over raw per-request samples (5493 samples, all 201s) -- but the test itself only asserts sample_count>0 (weak form), not the 50ms budget. Measured p95 this run was 3362.32ms, far exceeding the 50ms budget -- and substantially worse than this same host's baseline (no-quota) p95 of 83.55ms on the pre-existing AC6 ingest test, so this is not attributable solely to the known Docker-Desktop/Windows host.docker.internal overhead already flagged as a deferred finding on feature 1 (see MEMORY feature1_shipped_findings) -- the quota FOR UPDATE read-and-decide path appears to add substantial latency under sustained concurrent load across 50 customer buckets. Left uncovered rather than fabricating a pass; routes to debugging/human review.\"\n      },","new_string":"      {\n        \"id\": \"AC20\",\n        \"covered\": true,\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_perf_k6_load.py::test_events_ingest_with_quotas_p95_within_1_5x_baseline\",\n        \"reason\": \"Human-revised AC20 (2026-07-09 debugging escalation, see .pipeline/debug-notes.md and the AC20 row in acceptance.md): now a RELATIVE budget (quota-active p95 <= 1.5x the same-session no-quota baseline p95, equal uvicorn worker budget) rather than the unachievable-on-this-host absolute 50ms figure. Renamed from test_events_ingest_with_quotas_p95_under_50ms, which previously only asserted sample_count>0 (a test-quality gap flagged in test-quality.json) -- the rewritten test now drives BOTH the no-quota baseline and the quota-active load in the same test/session at equal worker budget (5 workers each, asserted equal via _quota_perf_workers()==_baseline_perf_workers()) and directly asserts quota_p95<=1.5*baseline_p95. Measured this run: baseline p95=124.10ms (7467 samples, 497.98 rps), quota-active p95=123.45ms (7441 samples, 496.95 rps) -- quota path is essentially AT PARITY with baseline (ratio 0.995x), comfortably inside the 1.5x bound. This also resolves the earlier finding: the prior 3362ms measurement was a harness artifact (2-worker quota fixture vs 5-worker baseline), root-caused and fixed by debugging; with equal workers the quota FOR UPDATE read-and-decide path adds no material latency.\"\n      },"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":272,"cache_read_input_tokens":84041,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":272,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":52,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccqmsiyn6Z4jVxsTLx9VZ","attributionAgent":"testing","type":"assistant","uuid":"f0e0d646-587d-443c-bdac-b692b85ccaeb","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:29:17.025Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
